.TH "efi_allocate_pages_aligned" 9 "efi_allocate_pages_aligned" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_allocate_pages_aligned \- Allocate memory pages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "efi_status_t" efi_allocate_pages_aligned
.BI "(unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long *addr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long max "  ","
.BI "unsigned long align "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "size" 12
minimum number of bytes to allocate
.IP "addr" 12
On return the address of the first allocated page. The first
allocated page has alignment EFI_ALLOC_ALIGN which is an
architecture dependent multiple of the page size.
.IP "max" 12
the address that the last allocated memory page shall not
exceed
.IP "align" 12
minimum alignment of the base of the allocation
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate pages as EFI_LOADER_DATA. The allocated pages are aligned according
to \fIalign\fP, which should be >= EFI_ALLOC_ALIGN. The last allocated page will
not exceed the address given by \fImax\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
status code
